# OpenTakeoff — web app environment
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in what you need:
#
#     cp .env.example .env.local
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠  EVERYTHING NAMED `VITE_*` IS PUBLIC.
#
# Vite inlines every `VITE_*` variable into the JavaScript bundle at build time,
# so its value ships to every visitor and is trivially readable in the browser.
# NEVER put a secret here — no client secret, no API key, no database URL, no
# access token. Only PUBLIC identifiers belong in this file: an OAuth client id,
# a Workspace domain, and Drive folder/file ids. (Google still gates who can
# actually use them — see docs/GOOGLE_SETUP.md.)
#
# Any real credential lives only in the out-of-band pricing sync job, never in
# the browser. See docs/GLIDE_INTEGRATION.md.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ALL OF THESE ARE OPTIONAL. With none of them set, OpenTakeoff runs exactly as
# it always has: an anonymous, local-only, client-side app — no account, no
# upload, everything in your browser. Setting the Google vars below is what
# unlocks the optional team-only cloud mode (Google sign-in + shared Drive).


# ── Contribution endpoint (pre-existing, optional) ───────────────────────────
# Where the optional "Contribute" button posts anonymized takeoff geometry.
# Leave unset and the button simply explains it isn't configured and sends
# nothing. Can also be set per-browser via localStorage.opentakeoff_contribute_endpoint.
# Required: no.
VITE_CONTRIBUTE_ENDPOINT=


# ── Team cloud mode: Google sign-in (all optional, all PUBLIC) ───────────────
# Setting these turns on the optional team-only cloud mode. Leave them
# blank to keep the app in anonymous local-only mode.

# The OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application) from Google Cloud. This is PUBLIC by
# design and is meant to ship in the bundle — the browser token-client / PKCE
# flow uses no client secret. Access is enforced by the OAuth consent screen
# being configured as Internal to your Google Workspace (see docs/GOOGLE_SETUP.md).
# Required: only for team cloud mode.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Your Google Workspace domain (the "hosted domain" hint). Google refuses login
# to any account outside this domain when the consent screen is Internal. This
# is the value that enforces "just our team."
# Example: 345flooring.com
# Required: only for team cloud mode.
VITE_GOOGLE_HD=example.com

# The Drive file id of `pricing.json` in the shared OpenTakeoff Drive. The app
# reads this file (material, unit, unit_cost) with the signed-in user's own
# Google token. A Drive file id is not a secret; Google still gates access.
# The file itself is produced by the out-of-band pricing sync job.
# Required: only if you want material costs in team cloud mode.
VITE_PRICING_FILE_ID=

# The Drive folder id of the team's "Projects" folder in the Shared Drive.
# Setting it (together with the client id above) enables the `/projects` route:
# a signed-in project browser for teammates to browse the folders inside it and
# open one as a project. It's reached through a subtle "browse team projects"
# link on the local canvas — `/` itself always stays the plain local canvas,
# never a sign-in wall. Leave blank to disable that route entirely. Note:
# folder SHORTCUTS inside it won't be listed — only real folders.
# Required: only for the project browser in team cloud mode.
VITE_DRIVE_ROOT_FOLDER_ID=
